<h3>Summary of New FCRA Provisions</h3><br>
	<ol start="1" type="I">
        <li>Before ordering information for employment purposes, an employer must:
		<ul>
        		<li>Disclose to the applicant in writing that a [consumer] report will be ordered</li>
        		<li>Obtain written consent to order any reports (see below for sample "Disclosure and Release" form)</li>
		</ul>
	</li>

	<li>Before refusing to hire an applicant based in whole, or in part, on report information an employer must:
		<ul>
        		<li>Notify the applicant of possible "adverse action"</li>
        		<li>Show the reports to the applicant and provide the applicant with a "summary of rights" notice</li>
        		<li>Provide oral, written or electronic notice of information included in the attached "Dear Applicant" letter</li>
                </ul>
	</li>
        </ol>  
